Interface ILoggerContext

    public interface ILoggerContext
    Interface to be implemented by classes capable of providing a logging context.

    A logging context in this sense is additional information to be stored in the logging system itself so that it may exist beyond the scope of a single log event.

    This class is similar in nature to org.slf4j.MDC, with the main exception being that it forces implementations to handle native long value types explicitly for efficiency.

    This interface defines some distinguished context keys which may be treated specially by some implementations in the logging subsystem. However, this interface does not define that special treatment or indeed which logging implementations provide such special treatment.
